**concerns:**
- Deck thumbnail srcdocs are injected manually after `tray.setFromPreset()` because `tray.js` is outside the allowlist. Any future internal tray re-render (e.g. `remove()`) will wipe deck thumbnails. The proper per-row srcdoc provider belongs to `tray-compose-spec` (future task).
- `?file=` arrival passes the raw filesystem path to `loadDeckByPath`; the e2e test converts backslashes to forward slashes for the URL. A user manually typing a Windows path with backslashes into the address bar may see browser-dependent behavior.
- The unsaved-tray replace guard uses a simple `confirm()` prompt; there is no actual dirty-tracking yet.

